  "prompt": "When the hydronium-ion concentration of a solution is 1\u00d710\u221212 M , what is the pH of the solution?",
  "response": "To calculate the pH of a solution when you know the hydronium ion concentration \\([H_3O^+]\\), you use the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{pH} = -\\log[H_3O^+] \\]\n\nGiven the hydronium ion concentration is \\(1 \\times 10^{-12}\\) M:\n\n\\[ \\text{pH} = -\\log(1 \\times 10^{-12}) \\]\n\\[ \\text{pH} = -(-12) \\]\n\\[ \\text{pH} = 12 \\]\n\nTherefore, the pH of the solution is 12.",
